            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><h3>Wet felting: Flowers</h3>
<p>Sunday, September 21 from 1 pm to 5 pm<br>
Ages 16 and up.<br>
Cost: $62.50 + tax (per person) .&nbsp;<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search/detail/150213?onlineSiteId=0&amp;locale=en-US&amp;from_original_cui=true"><strong>Advance registration is required.</strong></a></p>
<p>Learn to make felted flowers in a unique heritage setting. Led by Ann from Shepherds’ Spring Farm, you will combine merino wool and silk fibers to make felt using a wet felting process. You’ll then create two different styles of felted flowers, including making stems and stamens to add interest to your pieces. At the end of the workshop, participants will receive a pattern to inspire future projects at home. All skill levels, including beginners, are welcome. Supplies are included in the cost of registration; light refreshments will be served.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The primary language of delivery for this program is English.</li>
<li>There are two accessible parking spaces located in the parking lot closest to the museum. The workshop will take place outside on a grass lawn and under sun cover, or inside the museum on the main floor. There is an accessible bathroom located via gravel path. Additional&nbsp;<a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/node/1007490/">information about accessibility</a>&nbsp;can be found on the museum web page. If you have questions or concerns regarding accessibility, please contact the museum by phone at 613-832-4347 or by email at&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#d2bfa7a1b7a7bfa192bda6a6b3a5b3fcb1b3"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="58352d2b3d2d352b18372c2c392f39763b39">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>.</li>
<li>Advance registration is required. Workshops with insufficient registration may be cancelled. If an alternative cannot be offered, a refund will be issued.</li>
<li>Visit the&nbsp;<a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/family-and-social-services/older-adults/financial-assistance#section-89551f56-14c3-4f6e-b24c-5e5072350977">Ottawa Hand in Hand</a>&nbsp;web page for information on available financial supports to facilitate participation in recreation and culture programs.</li>
</ul>
